review_blob: Sweet aroma and dark brown to amber color. Drinks smooth with a little sweetness and a fruity flavor. Not easy to tell this is an 11.6% ABV.

Pour is dark brown/red with small head. Aroma is fruity and a little sweet. Taste starts off smooth then comes in sweet with a little alcohol bite, but nothing overwhelming. A really great beer. Highly recommended.
Totally average. Light orange pour, little to no head. Good aroma, floral sent. Flavor is unimpressive, slightly flat.
Tastes like an attempt at a Belgian without actually hitting the mark. Not a must drink, but not a definitely avoid either.
beer_name: Lagunitas Were Only In It For The Money

review_blob: Cloudy poor, crisp IPA like flavor, definitely hoppy. Not overwhelming and doesnt finish overly dry.
A perfect session beer. Mild carbonation and smooth nutty flavor. Purchased as a growler from Bierkraft in Brooklyn.
Just the right amount of spice, not overwhelming. A little sweet with a great aroma.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Farmhouse Ale
